    <Note Caller="1" LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="" LastEditedBy="">
      <References>
        <Reference>04900501100026</Reference>
      </References>
      <Content>If the direct object of the verb ἐλέγχω in {S:04900501100026} is understood as ‘those who have done the fruitless deeds of darkness,’ then the meaning is ‘rebuke.’ However, it is also possible to construe the direct object as being ‘the fruitless deeds of darkness,’ in which case the meaning of ἐλέγχω would presumably be ‘to expose by words.’</Content>
